Description: System error detected: ResolvertimeoutParameter _SigLatched Bit 22
Resolver velocity is too highParameter _SigLatched Bit 22
Encoder 2 Hall sensor error detectedParameter _SigLatched Bit 22
Cause: Incorrect wiring or inoperative cablefor Hall signals of encoder 2.

Description: Incorrect communication betweenmodule and encoderParameter _SigLatched Bit 22
Cause: Incorrect encoder wiring/adjustmentor incorrect encoder parametersettings (example: parameterENCDigSSICoding is set for SSIencoder).
Correctives: Verify encoder cable: wiring andshield connection.. Verify encoderparameter settings. Verify encoderadjustment.

Description: Incorrect communication betweenmodule and encoderParameter _WarnLatched Bit 22
Correctives: Verify encoder cable: wiring andshield connection.

Description: Connected type of EnDat encoder isnot supportedParameter _SigLatched Bit 22
Configuration error detected: InvalidSSI encoder parameter settingParameter _SigLatched Bit 22
Cause: Incorrect values in parameterENCDigSSIResSgl orENCDigSSIResMult.

Description: Maximum velocity of the encoder isexceededParameter _SigLatched Bit 22
Cause: Velocity too high for the encoder. Inthe case of SSI or EnDat2.2, thereason may also be a detectedencoder communication error.
The ambient temperature is too high.
Correctives: Improve the heat dissipation in thecontrol cabinet.

Description: Position evaluation error detected(AB encoder signals)Parameter _SigLatched Bit 22
Checksum error detected in EnDatencoder dataParameter _SigLatched Bit 22
Runtime compensation was notsuccessfulParameter _SigLatched Bit 22
Correctives: Verify encoder cable: wiring andshield connection.

Description: Absolute encoder signal is notavailableParameter _WarnLatched Bit 22
Cause: There is no encoder available at theinput specified via the parameterENC_abs_source.
Correctives: Verify wiring, verify encoder. Changethe value of the parameter ENC_abs_source.

Description: Absolute position for encoder 2cannot be setParameter _WarnLatched Bit 22
Cause: No encoder connected or encoderdoes not support setting of absolutepositions.
Correctives: Use an encoder that supports directsetting of the absolute position viaENC2_setpabs.

Description: Not possible to set the absoluteposition for encoder 1.Parameter _WarnLatched Bit 22
Cause: There is no encoder connected to theinput for encoder 1.
Correctives: Connect an encoder to the input forencoder 1 before trying to set theabsolute position directly via ENC1_abs_pos.

Description: Overflow error detected duringencoder scalingParameter _SigLatched Bit 22
Cause: The multiturn resolution of themachine encoder with reference tothe motor shaft exceeds the systemlimits, for example, due to themechanical gear ratio betweenmachine encoder and motor encoder.
Correctives: Reduce the number of bits of themultitun resolution that are used forposition evaluation via the parameterENCDigResMulUsed.
